00:54:19.850 --> 00:54:21.330
or other passive
investments such

00:54:21.330 --> 00:54:23.920
that essentially
you own everything.

00:54:23.920 --> 00:54:24.480
OK?

00:54:24.480 --> 00:54:26.610
So you're on the right
track, but the answer

00:54:26.610 --> 00:54:28.450
is not the SMP500.

00:54:28.450 --> 00:54:30.431
OK, good.

00:54:30.431 --> 00:54:30.930
Go ahead.

00:54:30.930 --> 00:54:34.419
AUDIENCE: I'm looking-- I'm
apartment shopping right now,

00:54:34.419 --> 00:54:36.419
[INAUDIBLE] potentially
purchasing an apartment,

00:54:36.419 --> 00:54:39.390
and it's really-- I feel
like I don't trust anyone.

00:54:39.390 --> 00:54:41.760
Which seems to be
the correct thing.

00:54:41.760 --> 00:54:43.460
I don't trust my
real estate broker,

00:54:43.460 --> 00:54:46.550
I don't trust my
mortgage broker.

00:54:46.550 --> 00:54:48.270
What should I do
to get past that,

00:54:48.270 --> 00:54:51.455
where I can make this decision
and feel good about it?

00:54:51.455 --> 00:54:54.170
STEPHEN BLUM: The
truth about negotiation

00:54:54.170 --> 00:54:55.730
that I didn't
mention is, we always

00:54:55.730 --> 00:54:58.160
have to make a
cost-benefit analysis.

00:54:58.160 --> 00:55:00.600
The book in my
classes teach you how

00:55:00.600 --> 00:55:02.610
to do a big,
important negotiation.

00:55:02.610 --> 00:55:06.160
And they say, invest a lot of
the resource of yourself in it.

00:55:06.160 --> 00:55:08.490
And so the answer I have
to give you involves

00:55:08.490 --> 00:55:10.490
investing a lot of
yourself and a lot of time.

00:55:10.490 --> 00:55:12.292
You might not choose to do it.

00:55:12.292 --> 00:55:14.500
But the answer that I've
been trying to present today

00:55:14.500 --> 00:55:15.800
is this.

00:55:15.800 --> 00:55:20.870
It's worth the effort to make
a huge research project out

00:55:20.870 --> 00:55:24.550
of finding particularly the
realtor, the one in a million

00:55:24.550 --> 00:55:28.000
realtors in New York, who really
behaves like a professional.

00:55:28.000 --> 00:55:30.790
Who really-- and you
have to find this

00:55:30.790 --> 00:55:33.230
through reputation and
through people who know them,

00:55:33.230 --> 00:55:34.730
or perhaps through
personal contact,

00:55:34.730 --> 00:55:37.690
but someone who will really do
as I said of a professional.

00:55:37.690 --> 00:55:39.980
Who will say, you are my client.

00:55:39.980 --> 00:55:41.450
You come first.

00:55:41.450 --> 00:55:44.660
And I don't have to make maximum
money off you, because if you

00:55:44.660 --> 00:55:47.060
go away saying, this is the
best realtor in New York

00:55:47.060 --> 00:55:51.040
and tell everyone who you know,
I'll do just fine in my career.

00:55:51.040 --> 00:55:51.870
OK?

00:55:51.870 --> 00:55:54.792
So the answer is, negotiate it.

00:55:54.792 --> 00:55:55.750
Like a real negotiator.

00:55:55.750 --> 00:56:00.810
And negotiate it means do your
research, do your finding out.

00:56:00.810 --> 00:56:01.900
Suss out the people.

00:56:01.900 --> 00:56:03.321
Learn, learn, learn.

00:56:03.321 --> 00:56:05.570
AUDIENCE: Who has the BATNA
in that situation, though?

00:56:05.570 --> 00:56:07.790
Because there's
a million buyers,

00:56:07.790 --> 00:56:09.249
but there's a
million brokers, too.

00:56:09.249 --> 00:56:11.289
STEPHEN BLUM: Well the
answer to BATNA analysis--

00:56:11.289 --> 00:56:13.100
and I really didn't
have time to do BATNA,

00:56:13.100 --> 00:56:15.300
BATNA takes me a
whole 3-hour lecture--

00:56:15.300 --> 00:56:18.910
but the answer to BATNA analysis
is, you always have a BATNA

00:56:18.910 --> 00:56:20.810
and they always have a BATNA.

00:56:20.810 --> 00:56:23.660
You always have an
answer to this question.

00:56:23.660 --> 00:56:26.650
After I've done all my
research and really examined

00:56:26.650 --> 00:56:29.000
my alternatives and
really thought hard

00:56:29.000 --> 00:56:32.240
about which is the best one,
I always have an answer.

00:56:32.240 --> 00:56:35.200
What will I do
after the research?

00:56:35.200 --> 00:56:37.180
What will I actually do?

00:56:37.180 --> 00:56:38.600
So what will you actually do?

00:56:38.600 --> 00:56:41.167
AUDIENCE: Just find someone
else or not [INAUDIBLE].

00:56:41.167 --> 00:56:42.000
STEPHEN BLUM: Right.

00:56:42.000 --> 00:56:43.416
And if you're
buying an apartment,

00:56:43.416 --> 00:56:45.417
obviously-- one of
the things I didn't

00:56:45.417 --> 00:56:47.750
talk about but I want you to
read the book and see about

00:56:47.750 --> 00:56:49.269
is strengthening your BATNA.

00:56:49.269 --> 00:56:50.810
You can always
strengthen your BATNA.

00:56:50.810 --> 00:56:52.800
The simple solution on
strengthening your BATNA

00:56:52.800 --> 00:56:56.450
is, know three places
you want to buy.

00:56:56.450 --> 00:56:59.619
And then knowing that, if I
can't reach a deal on this one

00:56:59.619 --> 00:57:02.160
because they're being jerks and
they're being New York realty

00:57:02.160 --> 00:57:04.110
people, I can buy this one.

00:57:04.110 --> 00:57:06.030
And I only fall this far.

00:57:06.030 --> 00:57:06.671
OK?

00:57:06.671 --> 00:57:07.170
Good.

00:57:07.170 --> 00:57:07.660
Sure.

00:57:07.660 --> 00:57:09.618
AUDIENCE: What's your
opinion of Robo-Advisors?

