STEPHEN BLUM: OK.

00:59:14.620 --> 00:59:17.312
There are a lot of
choices out there.

00:59:17.312 --> 00:59:19.270
Some of them are good
and some of them are not,

00:59:19.270 --> 00:59:21.410
so you're going to run
into the same problems.

00:59:21.410 --> 00:59:23.970
But it exists, and
it's there for you.

00:59:23.970 --> 00:59:25.964
But unfortunately of
course it's not perfect.

00:59:25.964 --> 00:59:27.880
The way it works, or the
way it tends to work,

00:59:27.880 --> 00:59:31.550
is investment choosers
work with screens.

00:59:31.550 --> 00:59:33.870
So lists are made of what
they will not invest in,

00:59:33.870 --> 00:59:35.744
and they invest in the rest.

00:59:35.744 --> 00:59:36.910
Some are better than others.

00:59:36.910 --> 00:59:40.350
My advice would be, in
light of efficient markets,

00:59:40.350 --> 00:59:42.640
you probably just want
to build your screen

00:59:42.640 --> 00:59:44.250
and invest in everything else.

