01:00:10.710 --> 01:00:13.670
STEPHEN BLUM: That
question goes to my point

01:00:13.670 --> 01:00:15.000
about the history is known.

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:16.000
And you can research it.

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:18.740
What you'll find is,
real estate does not

01:00:18.740 --> 01:00:22.590
return what common stocks
do over long periods.

01:00:22.590 --> 01:00:27.680
Let's take one minute and
talk about what is a stock.

01:00:27.680 --> 01:00:30.670
A stock is an ownership
interest in a company.

01:00:30.670 --> 01:00:32.330
And what is a company?

01:00:32.330 --> 01:00:37.540
A company is the coming together
of people, machines and capital

01:00:37.540 --> 01:00:39.470
under our laws for
solely one purpose.

01:00:39.470 --> 01:00:41.678
And hopefully it's a little
broader than one purpose,

01:00:41.678 --> 01:00:43.330
but our laws say
for one purpose.

01:00:43.330 --> 01:00:45.800
To try to make money.

01:00:45.800 --> 01:00:46.720
OK?

01:00:46.720 --> 01:00:47.540
They do.

01:00:47.540 --> 01:00:49.160
Not all of them do.

01:00:49.160 --> 01:00:50.310
Some fail.

01:00:50.310 --> 01:00:51.520
Some do poorly.

01:00:51.520 --> 01:00:53.910
But on average, they make money.

01:00:53.910 --> 01:00:55.580
And don't forget
what I'm advocating

01:00:55.580 --> 01:00:58.250
involves you're owning
essentially everything.

01:00:58.250 --> 01:01:01.970
So your broad portfolio
of everything of stocks

01:01:01.970 --> 01:01:03.850
is going to make
money, it's going

01:01:03.850 --> 01:01:07.420
to make the return that
companies make on average.

01:01:07.420 --> 01:01:09.746
And it turns out
that common stocks--

01:01:09.746 --> 01:01:11.120
these diversified
common stocks--

01:01:11.120 --> 01:01:13.982
is probably the best
investment you can make.

01:01:13.982 --> 01:01:15.940
On average, it will do
better than real estate.

01:01:15.940 --> 01:01:17.430
Because what is real estate?

01:01:17.430 --> 01:01:19.690
Real estate is sitting
there and it collect rents.

01:01:19.690 --> 01:01:23.510
But companies-- if this great
real estate to be had New York,

01:01:23.510 --> 01:01:25.390
you know who you're
competing with to buy it?

01:01:25.390 --> 01:01:26.706
Some real estate company.

01:01:26.706 --> 01:01:28.080
You can own stock,
you can become

01:01:28.080 --> 01:01:29.960
an owner of that
real estate company.

01:01:29.960 --> 01:01:32.160
OK?

01:01:32.160 --> 01:01:32.960
Good?

